returns._0: a list of all the function selectors that this logic extension exposes

acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

accruedManagementFee().details: Management fee is annualized per minute, based on 525,600 minutes per year. Total assets are calculated using  the average of their current value and the value at the previous fee harvest checkpoint. This method is similar to  calculating a definite integral using the trapezoid rule.

returns._0: Accrued management fee in underlying `asset` token.

accruedPerformanceFee().details: Performance fee is based on a high water mark value. If vault share value has increased above the   HWM in a fee period, issue fee shares to the vault equal to the performance fee.

returns._0: Accrued performance fee in underlying `asset` token.

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `amount` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

changeAdapters().details: This migration function will remove all assets from the old Vault and move them into the new vaultAdditionally it will zero old allowances and set new onesLast we update HWM and assetsCheckpoint for fees to make sure they adjust to the new adapter

decimals().details: Decimals are read from the underlying asset in the constructor and cached. If this fails (e.g., the asset has not been created yet), the cached value is set to a default obtained by `super.decimals()` (which depends on inheritance but is most likely 18). Override this function in order to set a guaranteed hardcoded value. See {IERC20Metadata-decimals}.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

estimatedAPR().details: It's computed by doing: `sum(nav * apr) / totalNav`

params.allocations: List of allocations (in bps of the nav) that should be allocated to each adapter

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

returns._0: Maximum amount of underlying `asset` token that may be deposited for a given address. Delegates to adapters.
Maximum amount of vault shares that may be minted to given address. Delegates to adapters.
Maximum amount of shares that may be redeemed by `caller` address. Delegates to adapters.
Maximum amount of underlying `asset` token that can be withdrawn by `caller` address. Delegates to adapters.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

previewDeposit(uint256).details: This method accounts for issuance of accrued fee shares.

params.assets: Exact amount of underlying `asset` token to deposit

returns._0: of the vault issued in exchange to the user for `assets`

previewMint(uint256).details: This method accounts for issuance of accrued fee shares.

params.shares: Exact amount of vault shares to mint.

returns._0: quantity of underlying needed in exchange to mint `shares`.

previewRedeem(uint256).details: This method accounts for both issuance of fee shares and withdrawal fee.

returns._0: quantity of underlying returned in exchange for `shares`.

previewWithdraw(uint256).details: This method accounts for both issuance of fee shares and withdrawal fee.

returns.shares: to be burned in exchange for `assets`

proposeFees((uint64,uint64,uint64,uint64.details: Fees can be 0 but never 1e18 (1e18 = 100%, 1e14 = 1 BPS)

params.newFees: Fees for depositing, withdrawal, management and performance in 1e18.

params.shares: Quantity of vault shares to exchange for underlying tokens.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._depositLimit: Maximum amount of assets that can be deposited.

setFeeRecipient(address).details: Accrued fees wont be transferred to the new feeRecipient.

params._quitPeriod: Time to rage quit after proposal.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

returns.assets: Total amount of underlying `asset` token managed by vault. Delegates to adapter.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner.

params.assets: Quantity of underlying `asset` token to withdraw.

returns._0: shares Quantity of vault shares burned in exchange for `assets`.

accruedManagementFee().notice: Management fee that has accrued since last fee harvest.

accruedPerformanceFee().notice: Performance fee that has accrued since last fee harvest.

harvest(uint64[]).notice: Harvests the Strategy, recognizing any profits or losses and adjusting the Strategy's position.

lentTotalAssets().notice: View function to check the total assets lent

pause().notice: Pause deposits. Caller must be Owner.

previewMint(uint256).notice: Simulate the effects of a mint at the current block, given current on-chain conditions.

previewRedeem(uint256).notice: Simulate the effects of a redemption at the current block, given current on-chain conditions.

previewWithdraw(uint256).notice: Simulate the effects of a withdrawal at the current block, given current on-chain conditions.

proposeFees((uint64,uint64,uint64,uint64.notice: Propose new fees for this vault. Caller must be owner.

redeem(uint256,address,address).notice: Burn exactly `shares` vault shares from `owner` and send underlying `asset` tokens to `receiver`.
